"{\"uid\": \"newsus.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-09-Breakdancing-debuts-at-Paris-Olympics-2024-1vULbA1o57G-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Frances Kuo  Copied  It's a dance with deep roots here in the United States.  Breakdancing, or \\\"breaking,\\\" originated in the 1970s in New York City \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 linked to the birth of hip-hop culture.  Now, decades later, it's making its debut at the Paris 2024 Olympics as a sport.  And it's partly because of one breaking veteran who helped pave the way.  CGTN's Frances Kuo reports.  For more, check out our exclusive content onCGTN Nowand subscribe to our weekly newsletter,The China Report.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"